The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Hospital veils

 London, Oct. 16 (PTI): 

 Birmingham hospitals have banned Muslim doctors from wearing 

 full-face veils.

 The Birmingham University School of Medicine had banned full-face veils to aid good communications. It said that Islamic women can cover their faces in lectures and around campus but not in clinical environments. 




